New Zealand beat England by 3 wickets with just 4 balls to spare in the 1st ODI at Hamilton.Batting first, England made 284 for 8.Jason Roy (49), Joe Root (71) and Jos Butler (79) propelled the visitor's total.In reply, Ross Taylor who scored his 18th ODI hundred ensured that the Kiwis reached the target in the 50th over.Tom Latham also made 79.